METHODOLOGY:
This bill repeals the Committee for the Protection of Human Subjects, and with it the
administrative support functions provided by the Department of Health and Human Services.
The Department states that administrative support is currently provided through a contract
with the Mental Health Center of Greater Manchester at an annual cost of $63,000 per year.
The Department anticipates that the bill will result in a net savings of $59,000 per year, as
$4,000 each year will still be needed to comply with federal rules regarding maintenance of
records. Although statute currently allows for the establishment of fees to fund administrative
support for the committee, the Department indicates that such support is currently generally
funded. The resulting cost reduction will therefore be a general fund savings. Since the bill as
amended takes effect January 1, 2027, this fiscal note assumes that only half of the savings will
berealizedinFY27.
